# Appendix B: Derivation of the SGD Effective Loss

**Lemma 3.1.** *Under $\Sigma(\theta) \preceq c \frac{\eta}{B} H(\theta)$ and small $\eta$, SGD minimizes $\mathcal{L}_{\text{eff}}(\theta) = \mathcal{L}(\theta) + \frac{\eta}{2B} \text{Tr}(H(\theta))$.*

**Proof.** The discrete update $\theta_{t+1} = \theta_t - \eta \hat{g}_t$ converges to the Itô SDE $d\theta_t = -\nabla \mathcal{L} dt + \sqrt{\frac{\eta}{B}} \Sigma^{1/2} dW_t$. The stationary density satisfies $p(\theta) \propto \exp(-\frac{2B}{\eta}\mathcal{L}(\theta)) \det(H(\theta))^{-1/2}$. Taking $-\log p(\theta)$ and using $\log \det(H) \approx \text{Tr}(H-I)$ near minima yields $\mathcal{L}_{\text{eff}}$. The approximation is local and assumes Hessian-aligned noise, empirically validated in overparameterized nets (Sagun et al., 2018; Karakida et al., 2019). $\square$

