# Appendix E: Linear Recombination & Error Bounds

**Proposition 6.1.** *With $\mathcal{P}_{G_1} F \mathcal{P}_{G_2} \approx 0$, output error satisfies $\| f_\theta(z_{\text{new}}) - \alpha f_{G_1}(z) - \beta f_{G_2}(z) \| \leq \mathcal{O}(\|\Pi_{G_1} z\|^2 \|\Pi_{G_2} z\|^2)$.*

**Proof.** Taylor expansion in the residual stream: $f_\theta(z_{\text{new}}) = f(0) + J z_{\text{new}} + \frac{1}{2}z_{\text{new}}^\top H_f z_{\text{new}} + \dots$. Cross-terms $\Pi_{G_1} H_f \Pi_{G_2}$ vanish under decoupling. Architectural normalization (LayerNorm/residual scaling) bounds higher-order terms, making the error second-order in subspace energies. $\square$

