# Appendix F: Empirical Validation Protocol

**F.1 Data Generation:** $P_{\text{common}}$: $10^6$ sequences from $\Sigma=\{0,1\}^8$ Markov chain. Rare Grammar $G$: CFG generating balanced brackets with logical constraints ($\epsilon \in \{10^{-5}, 10^{-6}, 10^{-7}\}$). Utility coupling: Inject $G$-derived logical tokens into 5% of $P_{\text{common}}$ to guarantee $\delta > 0$.

**F.2 Metrics & Probes:**
1. FIM block structure via Hutchinson estimator + randomized SVD; coherence $\rho = \|\mathcal{P}_G F \mathcal{P}_{\text{common}}\|_F / \|F\|_F$.
2. Hessian trace comparison: masked memorization vs. normal training.
3. Predictive utility ablation: zero out $\mathcal{P}_G \theta$; measure $\Delta \mathcal{L}_{\text{web}} \approx \delta$.
4. Recombination accuracy: perplexity + parser validity on novel $G$-constrained sequences.
5. Subspace persistence vs. $\lambda$: Validate collapse when $\lambda$ exceeds signal-to-decay threshold.

**F.3 Scaling Analysis:** Vary $D \in \{10^9, 10^{10}, 10^{11}, 10^{12}, 10^{13}\}$. Expect sharp drop in $\rho(D)$ and memorization/compression ratio flip at $D \approx \text{eff}(P_{\text{data}})$.

